This paper presents a method for legged robots to autonomously change their body shape to navigate confined spaces, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves mapping and planning strategies, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The path planning algorithm used is CHOMP, which is a popular optimization algorithm in robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses testing the proposed method in simulation and on a physical robot, which may involve machine learning techniques for training and evaluation (cs.LG).
